@startuml idempotency_flow
title Idempotency — First Request vs Retry (Deposit Example)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceArrowFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceParticipantPadding 20

actor "ATM Client" as ATM
participant "Middleware\n(/atm/deposit)" as MW
database "middleware_db\n(idempotency_records)" as DB
participant "Core Banking" as CB

== First request (Idempotency-Key: \"abc-123\") ==

ATM -> MW : POST /atm/deposit\nIdempotency-Key: abc-123\n{amount: 500}

MW -> DB : SELECT by (account_number, \"abc-123\")
DB --> MW : no record found

MW -> DB : INSERT\nstatus = \"in_progress\"\nrequest_fingerprint = SHA-256(...)\nexpires_at = now + 24h
DB --> MW : OK

MW -> CB : POST /accounts/{id}/deposit\n{amountDeposit: 500}
CB --> MW : 200 OK\n{transactionId, balanceAfter, referenceId, createdAt}

note right of MW
  Middleware builds the full response:
  hash, blockchain submit, etc.
end note

MW -> DB : UPDATE set status = \"completed\"\nresponse_body = {full JSON response}\ncompleted_at = now
DB --> MW : OK

MW --> ATM : 200 OK\n{status: \"SUCCESS\", amount: 500,\nnewBalance: ..., canonicalHash: ..., ...}

== Retry — same key, same body (network glitch) ==

ATM -> MW : POST /atm/deposit\nIdempotency-Key: abc-123\n{amount: 500}

MW -> DB : SELECT by (account_number, \"abc-123\")
DB --> MW : record found\nstatus = \"completed\"\nfingerprint matches

MW --> ATM : 200 OK\n{cached response — identical to first}\n**Core Banking is NOT called**

note right of MW #FFEEEE
  No duplicate deposit.
  The customer is not
  charged twice.
end note

@enduml
